snippet.textDisplay:
Never forget that the entire concept of FFP is BS. It was an invention of the biggest 10 clubs in Europe. A concept designed to ensure that they would stay at the top forever, barring horrible mismanagement. By making it impossible for teams lower in the leagues or in the lower divisions to spend their way to the top and CHALLENGE them! It builds in a permanent financial advantage to the biggest and most historic clubs, the ones the earn the most. By capping everyone to their revenue.

LIV were able to rise ONLY because they used to be great and built a worldwide fan base through the 70's and 80's. This provided them with TV and merch revenue not available to other mid table teams. They used that revenue wisely to modernize ANfield and further increase revenue. They then further used that additional revenue wisely to acquire high value \ return players. They then sold on several of those players ( Suarez, Sterling, and Coutinho ) for huge profits and then re-invested that revenue wisely yet again on WC players to address specific holes ( VVD, Keita, and Ali). All of which has won them a new generation of fans worldwide along with titles, resulting in yet even more revenue which undoubtedly will adequately the next gen rebuild over the next 2-3 years.

snippet.textDisplay: I don’t know if it’s just me but I hardly agree with what Geordie and most pundits have been saying about Newcastle this season. Geordie might not have watched every game to see tactically how poor we’ve been and how some results don’t accurately reflect Steve Bruce’s influence. However, that is absolutely fair enough because most games this season have been hard to watch. With that said, Joelinton not scoring this season is in large part down to how awful Steve Bruce is; we aren’t scoring because there’s no plan of attack and no service. Steve Bruce cannot sit here one year into managing our club and say he can’t change tactics yet. He can’t change tactics because he doesn’t have any. Furthermore, the only reason we are where we are is because of Almiron, ASM, Dubravka and some moments of brilliance by other players. I agree that we deserve to be worse off but how poor we are and have been is down to Bruce, Charnley and Ashley; not the players. We are playing lesser than the sum of our parts. The players we have now are too good to be playing the football that we are and to have us be where we are. I think Geordie should research and make a video on Steve Bruce and the state of our club to start a conversation on the clubs direction. As of right now we don’t have one and won’t get one without big names standing up. I know it won’t change anything immediately but we collectively have to stop going to games and buying merchandise to drive Ashley out. Nonetheless, this is a mint video and some great points were made about city.
